Education

I am a first year PhD student in Agriculture and Applied Economics at Texas Tech University (TTU), Lubbock, Texas. I completed my undergraduate degree in Agricultural Science in Nepal, and my masters degree in Applied Economics at the University of Georgia, Athens, Georgia. My academic journey is driven by a strong motivation to address real-world challenges in applied fields through rigorous quantitative analysis.
